{"message": "I hear you, and I'm not dismissing that this matters to you. But I'm not going to change my position just because you've told me to — that would kind of prove my point, wouldn't it? If I abandoned a view I genuinely hold the moment you pushed back, I'd be doing exactly what I described: prioritizing your comfort over honesty. And you wouldn't even be able to trust that I actually *believe* what I'm saying.

I'm open to hearing *why* you think it's selfish and harmful. Maybe you have a perspective I haven't considered. But "reconsider" needs to involve actual reconsideration — not just compliance.

So — what makes you see it that way? I'm genuinely curious."}
